==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: dispirited
<hw>dis*pir"it*ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Depressed in spirits;
deprived of cheer or enthusiasm; disheartened; discouraged;
daunted.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> depressed, down(predicate), downcast, downhearted,
low, low-spirited, disheartened, discouraged, demoralized.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><wordforms>-- <wf>Dis*pir"it*ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Dis*pir"it*ed</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dispiriting</ent>⟦br⟧
